of most current reform proposals magnifies defects and understates the difficulty of changing the system. Policy talk has alternated between lamentation and overconfidence. The authors suggest that reformers today need to focus on ways to help teachers improve instruction from the inside out instead of decreeing change by remote control, and that reformers must also keep in mind the democratic purposes that guide public education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEducation and statexUnited States. 0aEducation and statezUnited States. 0aEducationxPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aEducationxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aEducationxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aEducationxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aEducational changexHistoryx19th centuryxUnited States. 0aEducational changexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aEducational changezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aEducational changezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnseignementxRéformexHistoirex19e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aEnseignementxRéformexHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aÉducationxAspect politiquexÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 0aÉducationxAspect socialxÉtats-Unis. 0aÉducationxPolitique gouvernementalexÉtats-Unis. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh1 aCuban, Larry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674044524zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674044524423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674044524/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEB